posts.name: Basegio
posts.cooked: Where we are now.  The students constructed a simple prototype for use in understanding the changes for 2023.  They had this prototype (a couple of motors) running on the 2022 software. I took the prototype to try to implement 2023.  First problem was the FRC tools for the roboRIO Managed to get the FRC tools installed and the roboRIO firmware upgrade.  The next step was to update the Phoenix and RevRobotics libraries.  Ultimately the compile and link issues were resolved but unless directly connected via USB we could not see the CAN devices in the Phoenix tuner.  The program failed to deploy on my home system via USB or radio. I am the programming mentor - my home computer etc., could not update the radio - reason unknown.  One of the students took the equipment back to the school and was able to update the radio using the exact processes we had tried without success.  I won’t know until tomorrow night if they were successful in getting the program to deploy.

posts.name: Abhik Ray
posts.cooked:
Hey!

We’ve been having the same issue and got it to work today, heres a set of steps we followed:

Update Your Radio to the Latest 2023 Firmware using the Radio Configuration Utility

Update all your CTRE hardware to the latest 2023 season firmware (we made the mistake of accidentally using the “pro” versions, that is not necessary unless you of course have the licence)

Ensure your Phoenix Vendor Dependency is at the latest version (23.0.2 as of right now)

After we did these things (after making sure we had 2023 game tools & wpilib) we were good to go, hope this helps!
